void util_queue_async_insert (util_queue_t *queue, void *object)

Function Documentation

void util_queue_async_insert ( util_queue_t *  queue,
void *  object 
)

The util_queue_async_insert routine inserts an object into the queue. The object will always be referenced as the last object of the queue (FIFO).

NOTE: All objects which have to be queued require a simple void pointer (void*). This pointer is the first element of the object and will be used by the queue to handle the references to the next object of the queue (referenced list).

NOTE: The operation is not synchronized. There is no guaranty, that the operation will not be interrupted by another process or thread and another object will be inserted at this time. In this case the queue information can be corrupt.

Parameters:
queue Specifies the queue resource.
object points to an object which have to be inserted.
